My wife and I decided to have dinner near our hotel. Left Hand Path intrigued us. I drank Magners apple cider and had the brisket. Brisket is served with close slaw (creamy), mac and cheese, corn bread and a Guiness-based barbecue sauce. Huge serving. We’re from Kansas City, so we set high standards for brisket. This was fork-tender. My wife had fish and chips and a cocktail. Really a very good dinner.

Stumbled into this bar by chance, or perhaps fate. My party took seats at the bar, where we remained planted for several hours in conversation with the bar tenders, other patrons, and ourselves. We ended up blowing off our prior-arranged plans for the night across town rather than abandon the comfort we found here. Strong pours at an agreeable price, if you still need further convincing after those words of praise.

I've been here with close friends, acquaintances, and dates, and it never fails to deliver. They have a selection of about 15 beers on tap (many of which are Brooklyn-brewed) and the cocktails are always great as well. However, the best thing about this place is definitely the ambiance -- floor to ceiling wood paneling, nice warm lighting, and a chill, romantic back room if you're looking for a more intimate experience. One of the best bars in Bushwick for conversation/ambiance!

They will sell you wine by the bottle for a discount if you are a good customer. They will also pour you some water even though there is a water cooler in the corner by the stairs to the bathroom. Also--they allow outside food if it is homemade cake for a 30th birthday party in the back room.

Best bar in the hood, hands down! First, the bartenders are all great: friendly, fun, easy going, and serving up super good cocktails. Second, this place is super cozy, homey, and always filled with good folks having a good time. Third, it's all about that vintage sound system! Vintage EPI 100s pumping good tunes. So if you dig sound, come give a listen here. Forth, get their dumplings! Delicious. Finally, say 'hi' to Evan for me if he's behind the bar. Heart of gold that guy has.
